%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22CEOs%20are%20all%20in%20on%20AI%20%26amp%3Bmdash%3B%20even%20if%20no%20one%20knows%20what%20comes%20next%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224129%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20group%20of%20men%20in%20suits%20walking%20through%20downtown%20Manhattan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c9a9bff9db348adc0b937c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222754%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWorkers%20in%20downtown%20Manhattan%3Cp%3EBI%2FMomo%20Takahashi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECEOs%20of%20big%20US%20companies%20are%20more%20confident%20their%20AI%20investments%20will%20pay%20off%2C%20a%20KPMG%20survey%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENearly%2070%25%20of%20CEOs%20expect%20AI%20returns%20within%20one%20to%20three%20years%2C%20compared%20with%2021%25%20of%20CEOs%20in%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-not-afraid-ai-will-take-my-job-2025-9%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erise%20of%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20many%20leaders%20thinking%20about%20changes%20to%20corporate%20structures%20and%20worker%20training.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20thing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-co-ceos-us-companies-business-future-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eadvancing%20faster%20than%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20enthusiasm%20that%20many%20CEOs%20have%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20seven%20in%2010%20chief%20executives%20expect%20to%20see%20returns%20on%20their%20AI%20investments%20within%20one%20to%20three%20years%2C%20compared%20with%2021%25%20who%20held%20this%20view%20in%202024%2C%20KPMG%20US%20found%20in%20a%20recent%20survey%20of%20400%20heads%20of%20large%20US%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20underscores%20that%2C%20in%20only%20a%20year%2C%20CEOs'%20confidence%20in%20investing%20in%20AI%20has%20swung%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20to%20the%20other%20extreme%2C%26quot%3B%20Tim%20Walsh%2C%20the%20company's%20US%20chair%20and%20CEO%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20two%20in%2010%20leaders%20now%20expect%20to%20see%20returns%20in%20just%20six%20months%20to%20a%20year%2C%20up%20from%201%25%20last%20year.%20The%20latest%20survey%20took%20place%20from%20early%20August%20to%20mid-September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20growing%20anticipation%20over%20what%20AI%20can%20do%20is%20already%20reshaping%20how%20companies%20think%20about%20their%20business%2C%20Walsh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223556%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tim%20Walsh%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e43cab1c1f80efbec50764%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKPMG%20US%20chair%20and%20CEO%20Tim%20Walsh%20said%20that%20AI%20will%20bring%20change%20to%20workers%20across%20industries.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20KPMG%20US%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I%20am%20confident%20in%20is%20that%20every%20single%20layer%20in%20that%20labor%20stack%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20regardless%20of%20what%20industry%20you're%20in%20%E2%80%94%20is%20being%20disrupted%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20question%2C%20Walsh%20added%2C%20is%20how%20fast%20that%20change%20will%20unfold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2215c91bf2-b4e7-4eb1-8a7c-e8186ba4308f%5C%22%3EThe%20'hourglass'%20look%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20and%20especially%20the%20spread%20of%20AI%20agents%20that%20can%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etake%20on%20human%20work%20%E2%80%94%20will%20mean%20for%20corporate%20structures%20remains%20unclear%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20seven%20in%2010%20CEOs%20in%20the%20survey%20said%20they%20expect%20their%20organizations%20to%20start%20looking%20more%20like%20an%20hourglass%20%E2%80%94%20larger%20at%20the%20top%20and%20bottom%2C%20with%20a%20thinner%20middle.%20It%20wouldn't%20be%20atypical%20with%20new%20technology%20to%20see%20the%20mid-skill%20level%20be%20disrupted%20first%2C%20Walsh%20said.%20Yet%2C%20it%20would%20mark%20a%20shift%20from%20the%20traditional%20pyramid%2C%20where%20most%20workers%20sit%20closer%20to%20the%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it's%20too%20soon%20to%20say%20how%20a%20diet%20rich%20in%20AI%20might%20reshape%20companies.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20said%20the%20pyramid%20has%20been%20going%20away%20for%20years%20and%20years%20and%20years%2C%20and%20the%20pyramid%20is%20still%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Walsh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20he%20said%20it's%20possible%20that%20the%20look%20of%20many%20organizations%20could%20eventually%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20what%20extent%20is%20the%20question%2C%26quot%3B%20Walsh%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20the%20conversation%20I'm%20having%20with%20CEOs.%20We%20do%20not%20know.%20Nobody%20knows%20yet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20leaders%2C%20Walsh%20said%2C%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20understand%20what%20kinds%20of%20agents%20and%20technologies%20they%20can%20integrate%2C%20and%20what%20the%20ripple%20effects%20will%20be%20once%20they%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalsh%20said%20a%20goal%20for%20%26quot%3Bgood%20leaders%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20one%20he%20embraces%20%E2%80%94%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20when%20AI%20takes%20over%20certain%20tasks%2C%20the%20company%20helps%20affected%20workers%20develop%20new%20skills%20and%20move%20into%20new%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20get%20rid%20of%20%E2%80%94%20it%20is%20a%20retrain%20exercise%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalsh%20said%20the%20rapid%20pace%20of%20change%20is%20fueling%20concerns%20that%20AI%20could%20take%20people's%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20apprehension%20out%20there%20in%20the%20way%20people%20are%20speaking%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20employment.%20Ultimately%2C%20Walsh%20said%2C%20he%20expects%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20will%20be%20more%20opportunities%2C%26quot%3B%20not%20fewer%2C%20for%20human%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22148d2275-6bed-4725-b025-e7ca0143ca2f%5C%22%3EA%20focus%20on%20uncertainty%20and%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWalsh%2C%20who%20took%20on%20the%20top%20job%20at%20KPMG%20US%20in%20July%2C%20said%20that%20many%20of%20his%20conversations%20with%20a%20range%20of%20executives%20focus%20on%20uncertainty%3A%20how%20AI%20will%20actually%20reshape%20companies%20and%20when%20it%20will%20happen.%20The%20reason%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20the%20technology%20%26quot%3Bhasn't%20plateaued%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20still%20evolving%20and%20being%20woven%20into%20business%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20chiefs%20nevertheless%20expect%20that%20AI%20agents%20to%20result%20in%20big%20changes%20in%20how%20their%20businesses%20operate.%20In%20the%20survey%2C%2086%25%20of%20CEOs%20said%20agents%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bembedded%20team%20members%26quot%3B%20next%20year.%20About%20one-third%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20planned%20to%20cut%20jobs%20in%20some%20areas%20in%20the%20next%20two%20to%20five%20years%20because%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20AI%20agents%20on%20teams%20will%20mean%20processes%20get%20done%20differently%2C%20Walsh%20said.%20Often%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20technology%20will%20still%20require%20human%20oversight%20and%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20clients%20thinking%20about%20adding%20agents%20need%20to%20train%20employees%20in%20something%20that%2C%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20many%20companies%20%26quot%3Bwould%20never%20even%20have%20thought%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f8fb8ac-10b6-4c37-bb0e-31acbdcc7922%5C%22%3EMoving%20faster%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20isn't%20the%20only%20challenge%20for%20US%20leaders%2C%20Walsh%20added.%20Many%20are%20scrambling%20to%20remake%20supply%20chains%20to%20adapt%20to%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20nine%20in%2010%20said%20tariffs%20would%20significantly%20affect%20their%20business%20performance%20and%20operations%20during%20the%20next%20three%20years.%20Nearly%20as%20many%20said%20they%20plan%20to%20boost%20prices%20on%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20as%20needed%2C%20to%20offset%20the%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20broadly%2C%20Walsh%20said%20CEOs%20are%20focused%20on%20moving%20faster%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20a%20relentless%20pace%20of%20change%2C%C2%A0as%20well%20as%20enormous%20disruption%20and%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20his%20conversations%20with%20fellow%20CEOs%20often%20involve%20how%20to%20move%20forward%20in%20an%20environment%20%26quot%3Bwhere%20uncertainty%20and%20change%26quot%3B%20will%20be%20the%20norm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-more-confident-that-their-ai-investments-will-pay-off-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1759828501000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e41bea1c1f80efbec50462%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-more-confident-that-their-ai-investments-will-pay-off-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CEOs%20of%20big%20US%20companies%20are%20more%20confident%20that%20they're%20AI%20spending%20will%20pay%20off.%20What's%20less%20clear%20is%20how%20their%20organizations%20will%20look%20as%20a%20result.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-more-confident-that-their-ai-investments-will-pay-off-2025-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Diljit%20reveals%20release%20date%20of%20upcoming%20new%20album%20Aura%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1759828477000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22ht