onal's%20five-night%20stay%20at%20a%20hotel%20in%20New%20York%20is%20considered%20a%20service%20export%2C%20since%20it%20brings%20money%20into%20the%20country%20from%20a%20non-resident.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20the%20industry%20has%20produced%20a%20trade%20surplus%2C%20meaning%20that%20foreigners%20spent%20more%20visiting%20the%20United%20States%20than%20Americans%20spent%20abroad%20on%20travel.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%20that%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Einternational%20inbound%20travel%20has%20declined%2C%20the%20number%20of%20Americans%20traveling%20abroad%20has%20continued%20to%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-to-us-updated-advisories-canada-europe-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einternational%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20United%20States%20experienced%20a%20decline%2C%20the%20US%20Travel%20Association%20said%20the%20country%20was%20running%20at%20a%20%2450%20billion%20travel%20trade%20deficit%2C%20marking%20%26quot%3Ba%20sharp%20reversal%20from%20our%20historical%20surplus%20in%20travel%20exports.%26quot%3B%20In%202022%2C%20the%20United%20States%20had%20a%20%243.5%20billion%20travel%20trade%20surplus%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Commerce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20US%20Travel%20Association's%20travel%20forecast%20also%20said%20the%20number%20of%20international%20arrivals%20to%20the%20United%20States%20was%20expected%20to%20decline%20by%206.3%25%20in%202025%20compared%20to%202024%2C%20marking%20the%20first%20decline%20in%20inbound%20travel%20since%202020.%20Visitor%20spending%20was%20expected%20to%20decline%20by%203.2%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Travel%20Association%20said%20the%20decline%20in%20visitors%20from%20Canada%20was%20the%20primary%20driver%20of%20the%20decrease.%20Some%20Canadians%20began%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanadians-canceling-us-travel-earnings-visiti