%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20others%20rent%20out%20intelligence%20the%20way%20they%20rent%20cloud%20storage%20now.%20AI%20agents%20and%20custom%20models%20could%20form%20the%20basis%20of%20steady%2C%20high-margin%20subscription%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20doesn't%20pay%20off%3F%20Look%20no%20further%20than%20the%20railroads.%20Overinvestment%20in%20rail%20lines%2C%20including%20the%20Transcontinental%20Railroad%2C%20sparked%20not%20one%20but%20two%20banking%20crises%20in%20the%20latter%20half%20of%20the%201800s.%20The%20industry%20struggled%20with%20overspending%2C%20eventually%20leaving%20investors%20and%20the%20banks%20that%20had%20backed%20them%20with%20heavy%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20investment%2C%20the%20business%20case%20for%20AI%20is%20still%20untested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20infrastructure%20boom%20is%20built%20on%20a%20fundamental%20assumption%20about%20how%20machines%20learn%20best.%20The%20approach%20involves%20feeding%20massive%20amounts%20of%20data%20into%20large%20language%20models%2C%20which%20then%20look%20for%20patterns%2C%20or%20signals%2C%20buried%20in%20the%20noise.%20To%20improve%2C%20the%20theory%20goes%2C%20the%20models%20must%20ingest%20and%20analyze%20increasing%20amounts%20of%20data%2C%20which%20requires%20more%20and%20more%20computing%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20need%20for%20scale%20has%20shaped%20the%20competitive%20landscape.%20If%20better%20models%20depend%20on%20more%20computing%20power%2C%20the%20obvious%20next%20step%20is%20to%20secure%20as%20much%20of%20it%20as%20possible.%20And%20that%20means%20more%20data%20centers%20%E2%80%94%20large%20warehouses%20filled%20with%20graphics%20processing%20units%2C%20or%20GPUs%2C%20that%20handle%20the%20complex%20computations%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.samaltman.com%2Fabundant-intelligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20blog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20imagined%20what%20might%20be%20possible%20if%20AI%20systems%20had%20virtually%20unlimited%20computing%20power.%20AI%20could%20cure%20cancer%20or%20give%20every%20student%20on%20Earth%20a%20personalized%20tutor.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20are%20limited%20by%20compute%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe'll%20have%20to%20choose%20which%20one%20to%20prioritize%3B%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20make%20that%20choice%2C%20so%20let's%20go%20build.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20Marcus%2C%20a%20New%20York%20University%20professor%20emeritus%20of%20psychology%20and%20neural%20science%20and%20a%20vocal%20critic%20of%20Silicon%20Valley's%20approach%20to%20developing%20AI%2C%20has%20argued%20against%20the%20strategy%20that%20building%20bigger%20is%20better.%20Marcus%20has%20repeatedly%20argued%20that%20the%20fundamental%20theory%20driving%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20to%20build%20computing%20capacity%2C%20the%20scaling%20laws%2C%20is%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20meaning%20of%20the%20word%20scaling%20has%20been%20greatly%20devalued%2C%26quot%3B%20Marcus%20wrote.%20%26quot%3B'Scaling'%20used%20to%20mean%20'I%20can%20predict%20pretty%20much%20exactly%20how%20well%20a%20given%20LLM%20will%20do%2C%20by%20knowing%20the%20size%20of%20its%20database%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20compute%20being%20used%20to%20train%20it%2C%20and%20those%20increases%20will%20be%20exponential%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%26quot%3B%20Not%20anymore%2C%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI's%20August%20launch%20of%20GPT-5%2C%20its%20latest%20model%2C%20underscored%20Marcus'%20skepticism%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-openai-gpt-5-agi-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20perceived%20it%20as%20an%20incremental%20step%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20adding%20more%20computing%20power%20makes%20better%20models.%20The%20leading%20language%20models%20still%20make%20simple%20mistakes%2C%20or%20hallucinations%2C%20that%20hurt%20their%20reliability.%20The%20problem%20persists%20even%20as%20companies%20have%20poured%20exponentially%20more%20computing%20power%20into%20training%20them%2C%20according%20to%20Bain%20%26amp%3B%20Company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig-spending%20corporations%20have%20yet%20to%20show%20meaningful%20results%20aided%20by%20AI%2C%20several%20studies%20have%20concluded.%20Researchers%20at%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20published%20a%20report%20this%20summer%20suggesting%2095%25%20of%20early%20corporate%20AI%20initiatives%20had%20yet%20to%20deliver%20a%20return.%20Tech%20stocks%20briefly%20slumped%20on%20the%20report%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-ai-bubble-meta-sam-altman-mit-report-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eamong%20other%20reasons%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20at%20BetterUp%20Labs%20and%20the%20Stanford%20Social%20Media%20Lab%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bworkslop%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20the%20substandard%20AI-assisted%20product%20that%20more%20and%20more%20employees%20are%20producing.%20Because%20the%20models%20still%20lack%20accuracy%20and%20nuance%2C%20the%20task%20of%20fact-checking%20and%20cleaning%20the%20output%20falls%20to%20colleagues.%20Writing%20in%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20Review%2C%20the%20researchers%20said%2040%25%20of%20the%201%2C150%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkslop-oozing-americas-white-collar-offices-generative-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey%20surveyed%20reported%20having%20received%20%26quot%3Bworkslop%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20colleagues%20over%20the%20past%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20its%20utility%20still%20in%20question%2C%20it's%20not%20clear%20when%20or%20if%20the%20revenue%20to%20come%20from%20AI%20products%20will%20justify%20its%20spending.%20Bain%20estimates%20that%20by%202030%2C%20annual%20capex%20spending%20will%20be%20%24500%20billion%20to%20meet%20the%20industry's%20computing%20needs.%20To%20justify%20that%2C%20companies%20would%20need%20to%20generate%20%242%20trillion%20in%20annual%20revenue%2C%20Bain%20said.%20That's%20about%20%24800%20billion%20more%20than%20companies%20can%20save%20by%20using%20AI%20to%20make%20sales%2C%20marketing%2C%20customer%20support%2C%20and%20R%26amp%3BD%20more%20efficient.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20consulting%20firm%20concluded%2C%20the%20industry%20will%20come%20up%20short%20unless%20it%20can%20find%20new%20products%20or%20services%20to%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20Friar%2C%20OpenAI's%20CFO%2C%20said%20the%20company%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-exec-goldman-conference-numbers-chatgot-2025-9%3Fop%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etriple%20revenue%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20about%20%2413%20billion.%20That%20same%20month%2C%20the%20company%20agreed%20to%20pay%20Oracle%20an%20average%20of%20%2460%20billion%20a%20year%20for%20data%20center%20capacity%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20five%20times%20more%20than%20it%20expects%20to%20bring%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcKinsey%20%26amp%3B%20Company%20acknowledged%2C%20in%20an%20April%20report%20about%20capex%20spending%2C%20the%20difficult%20position%20the%20industry%20is%20in%3A%20Spend%20too%20little%20and%20risk%20missing%20out%20on%20a%20technology%20that%20may%20be%20one%20of%20the%20most%20transformative%20in%20history.%20Spend%20too%20much%20and%20risk%20wasting%20tens%20or%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stakes%20are%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20McKinsey%20wrote%20in%20the%20report.%20%26quot%3BOverinvesting%20in%20data%20center%20infrastructure%20risks%20stranding%20assets%2C%20while%20underinvesting%20means%20falling%20behind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20put%20it%20more%20bluntly%20when%20he%20admitted%20how%20much%20money%20he%20was%20prepared%20to%20waste%20to%20win%20the%20AI%20arms%20race.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20end%20up%20misspending%20a%20couple%20of%20hundred%20billion%20dollars%2C%20I%20think%20that%20that%20is%20going%20to%20be%20very%20unfortunate%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20told%20a%20podcast%20interviewer.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20underscored%20the%20risk%20of%20losing%20out%20if%20productive%20AI%20usage%20gains%20traction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20actually%20think%20the%20risk%20is%20higher%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20quarter%20of%20a%20century%20ago%2C%20a%20similar%20pattern%20emerged%20when%20firms%20rushed%20to%20lay%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20emerging%20internet.%20Companies%20like%20WorldCom%20and%20Global%20Crossing%20spent%20tens%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20in%20the%20five%20years%20through%202001%20laying%20fiber%20optic%20cables%20and%20installing%20other%20networking%20capabilities%2C%20only%20to%20crash%20the%20following%20year%20when%20the%20dot-com%20bust%20led%20lenders%20who%20had%20financed%20the%20construction%20to%20demand%20their%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShareholders%20in%20the%20companies%20leading%20the%20fiber-optic%20build-out%20lost%20%242%20trillion%20in%20value%2C%20while%20500%2C000%20workers%20lost%20their%20jobs%2C%20according%20to%20analysis%20conducted%20by%20the%20Brookings%20Institution.%20While%20the%20fiber%20optic%20cable%20was%20eventually%20put%20to%20use%2C%20largely%20by%20the%20streaming%20video%20revolution%20pioneered%20by%20Netflix%2C%20many%20of%20the%20companies%20that%20laid%20it%20weren't%20around%20to%20see%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20fiber%20optic%20cables%20and%20the%20railroads%20of%20an%20earlier%20era%2C%20data%20center%20construction%20and%20the%20purchase%20of%20GPUs%20are%20being%20financed%20by%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20money%20is%20coming%20through%20familiar%20channels.%20Oracle%20recently%20sold%20%2418%20billion%20worth%20of%20bonds%20to%20finance%20its%20data%20center%20expansion%20plans%2C%20while%20data%20center%20upstart%20CoreWeave%2C%20which%20went%20public%20in%20March%2C%20has%20tapped%20the%20public%20debt%20and%20equity%20markets%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20%2425%20billion%20since%20last%20year%20to%20fund%20its%20own%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20companies%20are%20also%20turning%20to%20less%20traditional%20lenders.%20Meta%20recently%20raised%20%2429%20billion%20for%20its%20latest%20data%20center%20project%20from%20firms%20including%20the%20Pacific%20Investment%20Management%20Company%20and%20Blue%20Owl%20Capital.%20The%20deal%20allowed%20Meta%20to%20raise%20billions%20without%20having%20to%20report%20the%20full%20amount%20on%20its%20balance%20sheet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Meta%20CFO%20Susan%20Li%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20company's%20plans%20for%20non-traditional%20financing%20methods%20at%20a%20recent%20conference%2C%20she%20said%20the%20company%20had%20built%20its%20own%20data%20centers%20for%20most%20of%20its%20history.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Now%2C%20she%20said%2C%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ambition%20of%20our%20infrastructure%20capacity%20unfolds%20ahead%20of%20us%2C%20it%20kind%20of%20dwarfs%20what%20we've%20built%20before%2C%20and%20we%20need%20to%20be%20sort%20of%20more%20expansive%20in%20the%20way%20that%20we%20are%20thinking%20about%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20data%20center%20developers%20are%20using%20the%20securitized%20bond%20markets%20to%20keep%20the%20boom%20going.%20Once%20a%20project%20is%20built%20and%20leased%2C%20they're%20turning%20the%20leasing%20revenue%20into%20bonds%20and%20selling%20to%20investors%20eager%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20AI%20boom.%20That%20frees%20up%20more%20money%20to%20put%20into%20future%20projects%20and%20fuels%20the%20spending%2C%20even%20if%20demand%20for%20mature%20data%20center%20projects%20starts%20to%20wane%2C%20said%20Paul%20Kedrosky%2C%20a%20financial%20blogger%20and%20advisor%20to%20hedge%20funds%20who%20recently%20wrote%20about%20the%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDevelopers%20build%20data%20centers%2C%20lease%20access%20to%20hyperscalers%2C%20and%20then%20package%20the%20rental%20income%20into%20bonds.%20Proceeds%20are%20recycled%20into%20the%20next%20round%20of%20construction%2C%26quot%3B%20Kedrosky%20wrote%20on%20his%20website.%20%26quot%3BIn%20short%3A%20the%20structured-credit%20world%2C%20not%20the%20real%20estate%20equity%20one%2C%20now%20finances%20the%20data-center%20boom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20Silicon%20Valley%20itself%20is%20helping%20to%20finance%20the%20boom.%20In%20September%2C%20Nvidia%20agreed%20to%20invest%20%24100%20billion%20into%20OpenAI%20to%20help%20with%20its%20data%20center%20build-out%2C%20with%20the%20expectation%20that%20OpenAI%20would%20turn%20around%20and%20use%20the%20money%20to%20purchase%20Nvidia's%20GPUs%20for%20its%20data%20centers.%20Microsoft%20invested%20in%20OpenAI%20early%2C%20and%20OpenAI%20used%20the%20money%20to%20rent%20out%20Microsoft's%20computing%20capacity.%20On%20Monday%2C%20chipmaker%20AMD%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fir.amd.com%2Fnews-events%2Fpress-releases%2Fdetail%2F1260%2Famd-and-openai-announce-strategic-partnership-to-deploy-6-gigawatts-of-amd-gpus%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20OpenAI%20has%20agreed%20to%20buy%20GPUs%20to%20power%20as%20many%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famd-stock-price-openai-deal-nvidia-chips-gpus-nvda-ai-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E6%20gigawatts%20of%20computing%20capacity%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20return%20for%20a%20warrant%20that%20would%20give%20OpenAI%20a%2010%25%20stake%20in%20the%20chipmaker%20if%20it%20hits%20certain%20milestones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20partnership%20is%20a%20major%20step%20in%20building%20the%20compute%20capacity%20needed%20to%20realize%20AI's%20full%20potential%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20said%20in%20the%20statement%20announcing%20the%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20circular%20flow%20of%20money%20is%20yet%20another%20element%20of%20the%20AI%20infrastructure%20bet%20that%20underscores%20its%20scale%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20risks.%20If%20the%20hype%20around%20AI%20proves%20fleeting%20%E2%80%94%20if%20more%20computing%20power%20doesn't%20equate%20to%20better%20models%2C%20or%20the%20industry%20can't%20find%20more%20ways%20to%20make%20more%20money%20%E2%80%94%20the%20interlocking%20investments%20could%20magnify%20the%20fallout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20proponents%20of%20AI%20say%20the%20math%20is%20daunting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20bullish%20on%20this%20in%20a%20big%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Crawford%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20Bain's%20technology%20practice.%20%26quot%3BThe%20point%20we%20were%20trying%20to%20make%20is%20that%20it's%20expensive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-ai-capex-infrastructure-data-center-wars-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1759824722000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6824f56a3fe8d3928365de60%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-ai-capex-infrastructure-data-center-wars-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Big%20Tech%20is%20set%20to%20spend%20%24320%20billion%20on%20capex%2C%20mainly%20for%20AI%20infrastructure%20like%20data%20centers.%20It's%20a%20construction%20boom%20unlike%20any%20in%20living%20memory.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dcampbell%2Bweb%40insider.com%20(Dakin%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-ai-capex-infrastructure-data-center-wars-2025-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Planning%20a%20vacation%20was%20already%20a%20nightmare.%20Then%20came%20AI.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20robot%20outside%20an%20airplane%20window%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e4146f1c1f80efbec5030f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20booked%20my%20vacation%20this%20year%2C%20I%20spent%20about%20a%20month%20tracking%20flights%20and%20weighing%20various%20layover%20scenarios%2C%20and%20eventually%20used%20a%20year's%20worth%20of%20hoarded%20credit%20card%20points%20plus%20about%20%24280%20out%20of%20pocket%20to%20get%20a%20flight%20in%20an%20economy%20seat%20to%20Croatia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECould%20this%20all%20have%20been%20easier%20and%20cheaper%20if%20I'd%20used%20AI%3F%20It's%20possible%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-amd-deal-highlights-ai-strain-on-power-grid-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eartificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20played%20a%20role%20in%20what%20I%20booked%20and%20paid.%20AI%20has%20seeped%20into%20every%20corner%20of%20the%20travel%20industry%3A%20It's%20pricing%20flights%2C%20examining%20dents%20on%20rental%20cars%20with%20eagle-eyed%20precision%2C%20blocking%20suspicious-looking%20Airbnb%20bookings%2C%20and%20parsing%20the%20air%20in%20hotel%20rooms%20for%20signs%20of%20sneaky%20smokers.%20For%20travel%20companies%2C%20AI%20is%20the%20vigilant%20cost-cutter.%20For%20travelers%2C%20however%2C%20it's%20a%20more%20ambivalent%20tagalong%3A%20AI%20could%20be%20a%20personalized%20travel%20agent%2C%20or%20it%20could%20be%20a%20restrictive%20chaperone%20monitoring%20every%20part%20of%20your%20trip%20and%20sometimes%20hitting%20you%20with%20higher%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20already%20a%20lack%20of%20transparency%20for%20people%20to%20understand%20the%20costs%20of%20their%20trip%2C%20and%20that%20only%20gets%20murkier%20once%20LLMs%20are%20involved%20internally%20at%20companies.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20question%20of%20how%20are%20they%20doing%20it%20behind%20the%20scenes%20efficiently%3F%26quot%3B%20Ari%20Lightman%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Carnegie%20Mellon%20University's%20Heinz%20College%20of%20Information%20Systems%20and%20Public%20Policy%2C%20says%20of%20travel%20companies%20using%20AI.%20%26quot%3BAre%20they%20doing%20it%20in%20your%20best%20interests%20or%20are%20they%20doing%20it%20in%20their%20best%20interests%3F%20Sometimes%2C%20they%20don't%20match.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelta-one-europe-us-review-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equestion%20facing%20Delta%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20summer%2C%20when%20the%20airline%20told%20investors%20that%20it%20has%20begun%20using%20generative%20AI%20to%20determine%20prices%20of%20about%203%25%20of%20its%20US%20flights%2C%20and%20planned%20to%20expand%20that%20to%20cover%20about%20a%20fifth%20of%20routes%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20There%20was%20immediate%20pushback%2C%20including%20a%20letter%20from%20US%20senators%20expressing%20concern%20that%20the%20plan%20would%20lead%20to%20price%20increases%20%26quot%3Bup%20to%20each%20individual's%20'pain%20point.'%26quot%3B%20Delta%20clarified%20later%20that%20it%20has%20not%20and%20does%20not%20plan%20to%20use%20an%20individual%20pricing%20model%20based%20on%20customers'%20personal%20data%2C%20but%20using%20AI%20to%20set%20prices%20based%20on%20aggregate%20purchasing%20data%20for%20specific%20routes%20and%20flights%20and%20to%20forecast%20demand%20%E2%80%94%20the%20tech%20%26quot%3Brecommends%20pricing%20adjustments%20in%20both%20directions%20to%20enhance%20market%20competitiveness%20and%20drive%20sales%2C%20benefiting%20both%20our%20customers%20and%20our%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20company.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20update%20to%20dynamic%20pricing%2C%20a%20longstanding%20part%20of%20the%20travel%20industry%20where%20prices%20rise%20and%20fall%20based%20on%20factors%20like%20booking%20date%20and%20demand.%20But%20it's%20clear%20this%20move%20is%20just%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20more%20efficient%20pricing%20tool%20for%20Delta%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20data%20it%20has%2C%20and%20the%20more%20cases%20we%20give%20it%2C%20the%20more%20it%20learns%2C%20and%20we're%20really%20excited%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Delta%20president%20Glen%20Hauenstein%20told%20investors%20in%20July.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20already%20detest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-dynamic-pricing-surge-cost-fatigue-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edynamic%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Ticketmaster%2C%20rideshare%20apps%2C%20and%20even%20Wendy's%20have%20irked%20many%20with%20erratic%20costs.%20Travelers%20can%20try%20to%20track%20price%20changes%20with%20Google%20Flights%2C%20but%20ultimately%20can't%20know%20they're%20getting%20the%20best%20deal%20when%20they%20pull%20the%20trigger.%20There%20are%20some%20winners%2C%20and%20some%20very%20frustrated%20losers%20(a%20friend%20and%20I%20just%20booked%20the%20same%20flight%20within%20minutes%20of%20one%20another%20last%20month%20%E2%80%94%20he%20paid%20%2484%2C%20checked%20bag%20included%2C%20I%20paid%20%24103%20for%20no%20bag).%20Dynamic%20pricing%20with%20gen%20AI%20means%20those%20shifts%20can%20happen%20much%20quicker%2C%20says%20Richie%20Karaburun%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20New%20York%20University's%20SPS%20Tisch%20Center%20of%20Hospitality.%20Now%2C%20customers%20might%20see%20them%20flip%20%26quot%3Bnot%20on%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20not%20hourly%2C%20but%20on%20a%20minutes%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20isn't%20just%20acting%20like%20the%20middleman%20for%20price%20bargaining%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20also%20checking%20to%20make%20sure%20travelers%20behave.%20Car%20rental%20company%20Hertz%20deployed%20UVeye%2C%20an%20AI%20vehicle%20scanner%20to%20check%20for%20dings%20and%20scrapes%20on%20its%20cars.%20Emily%20Spencer%2C%20a%20Hertz%20spokesperson%2C%20tells%20me%20in%20an%20email%20that%20the%20old%20way%20of%20doing%20inspections%20%26quot%3Bcaused%20confusion%20and%20frustration%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bwas%20manual%2C%20subjective%2C%20and%20inconsistent.%26quot%3B%20The%20new%20system%20brings%20%26quot%3Bprecision%2C%20objectivity%2C%20and%20transparency%20to%20the%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Spencer%20says.%20%26quot%3BOur%20goal%20through%20this%20initiative%20is%20to%20enhance%20the%20safety%2C%20quality%2C%20and%20reliability%20of%20our%20fleet%20and%20to%20create%20a%20more%20consistent%20rental%20experience%20for%20our%20customers.%26quot%3B%20Hertz%20has%20scanned%20nearly%201%20million%20cars%20so%20far%2C%20and%20more%20than%2097%25%20had%20no%20billable%20damage.%20Hertz%20did%20not%20answer%20questions%20I%20asked%20about%20the%20amount%20of%20times%20the%20tech%20has%20wrongfully%20flagged%20damage%2C%20but%20says%20its%20customer%20support%20team%20deals%20with%20disputes.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbnb%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20been%20using%20AI%20in%20recent%20years%20to%20block%20bookings%20that%20may%20be%20for%20parties%2C%20looking%20at%20a%20user's%20age%2C%20length%20of%20the%20booking%2C%20and%20how%20close%20they%20live%20to%20the%20property%20%E2%80%94%20all%20data%20points%20the%20company%20says%20can%20align%20with%20those%20who%20do%20throw%20parties.%20By%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20the%20company%20reported%20a%2054%25%20decrease%20in%20the%20rate%20of%20all%20party%20reports%20in%20the%20US%20since%202020.%20That%20could%20stop%20people%20from%20damaging%20a%20host's%20property%2C%20or%20it%20might%20block%20a%20legitimate%20stay.%20I%20asked%20Airbnb%20for%20data%20on%20the%20number%20of%20booking%20attempts%20incorrectly%20flagged%20as%20parties%2C%20but%20the%20company%20did%20not%20provide%20it%20(although%20Airbnb%20does%20say%20people%20who%20have%20been%20blocked%20incorrectly%20can%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20company's%20support%20team%20to%20try%20to%20fix%20a%20reservation).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETravelers%20who%20want%20to%20hack%20the%20system%20back%20are%20using%20AI%20to%20try%20to%20save%20time%20and%20money.%20There's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusing-ai-tool-for-trip-planning-honeymoon-mindtrip-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMindtrip%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20personalized%20travel%20itineraries%2C%20Gondola%2C%20which%20pulls%20your%20reward%20points%20from%20your%20email%20and%20tries%20to%20find%20the%20best%20travel%20deals%2C%20and%20companies%20like%20Kayak%20that%20use%20ChatGPT%20as%20a%20virtual%20assistant.%20Expedia%20has%20been%20using%20personalized%20recommendations%20for%20years%2C%20but%20it%20now%20has%20an%20AI%20customer%20service%20agent%20handling%20143%20million%20conversations%20each%20year%2C%20and%20another%20tool%20that%20crafts%20vacation%20itineraries%20from%20Instagram%20reels%20%E2%80%94%20making%20that%20social%20media%20idealized%20vacation%20closer%20to%20a%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20virtual%20travel%20agent%20is%20yet%20to%20take%20flight%3A%20In%202024%2C%2047%25%20of%20people%2034%20and%20younger%20said%20they%20felt%20comfortable%20using%20AI%20to%20plan%20a%20trip%2C%20the%20most%20of%20any%20age%20group%2C%20according%20to%20a%20YouGov%20survey%20of%20700%20adults.%20In%202025%2C%20that%20fell%20to%2034%25%20for%20adults%2024%20and%20younger%2C%20and%2038%25%20for%20people%20ages%2025%20to%2034%2C%20according%20to%20a%20July%20iteration%20of%20the%20survey.%20SEO%20Travel%2C%20a%20marketing%20consultant%20company%20in%20England%2C%20generated%20100%20travel%20itineraries%20with%20ChatGPT%20last%20year%20and%20found%20that%2090%25%20of%20them%20had%20at%20least%20one%20error%20%E2%80%94%20including%20attractions%20that%20are%20permanently%20closed%20or%20suggestions%20to%20visit%20places%20outside%20of%20their%20business%20hours.%20Last%20year%2C%20I%20reported%20on%20a%20walking%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Flittlefoot-ai-chatbot-travel-planner%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etour-focused%20chatbot%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20asking%20for%20recommendations%20on%20a%20day%20around%20New%20York%20City%20with%20my%20dog%2C%20and%20it%20gave%20me%20complicated%20itineraries%20that%20involved%20long%20walks%20and%20subway%20rides%20that%20criss-crossed%20back%20and%20forth%20between%20boroughs%2C%20and%20the%20chatbot%20repeatedly%20suggested%20activities%20that%20aren't%20dog%20friendly%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20spin%20class.%20I%20am%20not%20the%20only%20traveler%20led%20astray%2C%20there%20are%20reports%20of%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Ftravel%2Farticle%2F20250926-the-perils-of-letting-ai-plan-your-next-trip%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraveling%20to%20Peru%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20hike%20mountains%20that%20don't%20exist%20or%20getting%20duped%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F91368492%2Fai-video-tricking-tourists-places-that-dont-exist%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egenerative%20AI%20videos%20of%20fake%20places%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Hauenstein%20of%20Delta%20said%2C%20the%20AI%20models%20are%20only%20as%20good%20as%20what%20they've%20learned.%20That%20gap%20might%20hurt%20travelers%20in%20the%20short-term.%20%26quot%3BYou%20need%20foundational%20data%20for%20any%20of%20these%20LLMs%20to%20work%20or%20any%20AI%2C%20and%20how%20do%20you%20provide%20the%20most%20clean%2C%20standardized%2C%20complete%2C%20accurate%20set%20of%20data%20for%20the%20models%20to%20train%20off%20of%3F%26quot%3B%20says%20Andy%20Frawley%2C%20CEO%20of%20Data%20Axle%2C%20a%20data%20marketing%20company.%20But%20if%20those%20data%20sets%20do%20improve%2C%20there's%20potential%20for%20AI%20to%20work%20for%20both%20travelers%20and%20travel%20companies%20by%20helping%20to%20connect%20the%20right%20ones%20together.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20have%20a%20trip%20planned%20and%20I've%20got%20a%20%245%2C000%20budget%2C%20who%20can%20capture%20most%20of%20the%20%245%2C000%20budget%3F%26quot%3B%20Frawley%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20where%20I%20think%20using%20AI%20to%20build%20that%20experiential%20part%20of%20the%20trip%20is%20where%20in%20the%20short%20term%20there's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20big%20difference.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20might%20make%20your%20trip%20more%20expensive%2C%20or%20it%20might%20find%20you%20a%20deal.%20It's%20becoming%20harder%20to%20know%20if%20you're%20on%20the%20winning%20or%20the%20losing%20side%20of%20the%20coin.%20When%20companies%20push%20AI%20into%20their%20systems%20in%20the%20name%20of%20efficiency%2C%20they%20run%20the%20risk%20of%20going%20too%20far.%20What's%20good%20for%20the%20bottom%20line%20isn't%20always%20good%20for%20customer%20morale.%20And%20travel%20purchases%20are%20tied%20to%20our%20emotions.%20Away%20from%20home%2C%20travelers%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20when%20flights%20are%20delayed%20or%20hotels%20overbooked%3A%20it's%20not%20just%20a%20missed%20experience%2C%20but%20an%20issue%20that%20can%20strand%20them.%20A%20bad%20experience%20%26quot%3Bhas%20ripple%20effects%20associated%20with%20the%20entire%20vacation%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Lightman.%20A%20long%20line%20for%20one%20attraction%20might%20mean%20you%20miss%20the%20next%2C%20a%20rental%20car%20snafu%20could%20make%20you%20late%20to%20a%20wedding.%20A%20bad%20vacation%20memory%20can%20be%20just%20as%20impactful%20as%20a%20good%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%20covering%20the%20tech%20industry.%20She%20writes%20about%20the%20biggest%20tech%20companies%20and%20trends.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplanning-vacation-nightmare-then-came-ai-plane-pricing-airbnb-2025-10%5C%22%3EB