ook-americans-wealthy-consumer-spending-stocks-job-market-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eother%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealthy-americans-spend-lower-income-cut-back-affordability-earnings-consumers-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20are%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20money.%20I%20think%20the%20causality%20here%20is%20backward.%20A%20consumer%20slowdown%20is%20never%20the%20precipitating%20cause%20of%20an%20economic%20slump.%20Usually%2C%20consumption%20falls%20after%20employment%20materially%20cracks.%20When%20Americans%20stop%20spending%2C%20by%20that%20time%2C%20it's%20already%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-doomers-and-market-bears-in-brutal-losing-streak-slok-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmericans%20continue%20to%20spend%3C%2Fa%3E%20their%20way%20through%20their%20troubles%2C%20it%20may%20not%20prevent%20an%20economic%20slump%20from%20taking%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20notion%20that%20consumer%20spending%20can%20save%20the%20country%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-recession-odds-outlook-building-permits-mark-zandi-rate-cuts-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20recession%3C%2Fa%3E%20contradicts%20several%20historical%20trends.%20For%20starters%2C%20consumption%20has%20managed%20to%20grow%20modestly%20in%20previous%20economic%20slumps.%20In%20several%20of%20the%20post-World%20War%20II%20recessions%20%E2%80%94%201948%2C%201970%2C%201982%2C%20and%202001%20%E2%80%94%20real%20consumption%20expanded%20%3Cem%3Eduring%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20downturn.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20during%20those%20recessions%2C%20the%20best%20that%20spending%20could%20do%20was%20to%20help%20economic%20conditions%20from%20deteriorating%20further%2C%20cushioning%20the%20blow%20rather%20than%20preventing%20it%20altogether.%20In%20other%20periods%20of%20negative%20growth%2C%20consumption%20declined%20substantially%2C%20so%20that%20on%20average%2C%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-spending-race-capex-gdp-us-economy-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econtribution%20to%20GDP%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20recessions%20is%20close%20to%20zero.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20consumption%20has%20never%20declined%20before%20an%20economic%20slump%3B%20it's%20always%20happened%20%3Cem%3Eafter%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20economy%20began%20to%20go%20into%20the%20tank.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20growth%20in%20recent%20quarters%20does%20not%20look%20especially%20unusual.%20Assuming%20tracking%20estimates%20for%20the%20current%20quarter%20end%20up%20in%20the%20ballpark%2C%20average%20annualized%20growth%20in%20real%20consumer%20spending%20is%20expected%20to%20run%20at%20about%202.2%25%20in%20the%20first%20two%20quarters%20of%202025.%20This%20is%20slightly%20slower%20than%20consumption%20growth%20in%20the%20two-quarter%20period%20preceding%20each%20of%20the%20last%20three%20recessions%2C%20but%20it's%20hardly%20out%20of%20the%20ordinary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F7onhc%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Bar%20Chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F7onhc%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20deepen%20this%20analysis%20by%20breaking%20out%20the%20various%20types%20of%20major%20spending%3A%20durable%20goods%2C%20such%20as%20washing%20machines%20and%20TVs%3B%20nondurable%20goods%20like%20T-shirts%20and%20groceries%3B%20and%20services%2C%20encompassing%20everything%20from%20restaurants%20to%20movie%20tickets.%20Prior%20to%20previous%20recessions%2C%20the%20most%20common%20signal%20from%20these%20categories%20was%20Americans%20cutting%20back%20on%20big-ticket%20durables%20rather%20than%20cutting%20spending%20in%20service%20industries.%20As%20our%20figure%20shows%2C%20going%20back%20over%20the%20past%2011%20cycles%2C%20people%20decreased%20their%20expenditures%20on%20durable%20goods%20in%20the%20two%20quarters%20preceding%20the%20recession%20just%20over%20half%20the%20time.%20And%20during%20recessions%2C%20durable%20goods%20spending%20tends%20to%20fall%20while%20spending%20on%20services%20holds%20up.%20So%20far%20this%20year%2C%20spending%20on%20durables%20has%20been%20about%20flat.%20At%20the%20very%20least%2C%20this%20suggests%20a%20degree%20of%20caution%20among%20Americans%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20making%20big-ticket%20spending%20decisions%20that%20could%20portend%20more%20trouble%20coming%20down%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20confounding%20variable%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-latest-updates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump's%20herky-jerky%20tariff%3C%2Fa%3E%20announcements%20are%20influencing%20the%20data%2C%20creating%20a%20push%20and%20pull%20in%20consumer%20behavior%20regarding%20durables.%20The%20threat%20of%20tariffs%20may%20have%20prompted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretail-food-services-car-sales-dropped-trump-tariffs-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epeople%20to%20pull%20forward%20activity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20big%20purchases%20before%20anticipated%20price%20hikes%2C%20while%20the%20hope%20for%20tariff%20removals%20might%20cause%20consumers%20to%20wait%20it%20out.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20big%20story%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%20this%20year%20has%20been%20the%20slowing%20of%20services%20spending%2C%20which%20is%20likely%20less%20sensitive%20to%20tariff%20news.%20This%20suggests%20that%20if%20you're%20waiting%20for%20the%20consumer%20to%20make%20a%20call%20about%20a%20turn%20in%20the%20business%20cycle%2C%20you're%20likely%20waiting%20too%20long.%20The%20recession%20red%20light%20is%20already%20lit%20by%20the%20time%20consumption%20contracts%2C%20and%20sometimes%20it%20does%20not%20fall%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff14efc7-b82d-4aa3-8881-c84a76744046%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmerica's%20job%20market%20is%20looking%20weak%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20better%20indicator%20to%20watch%2C%20if%20you%20were%20trying%20to%20anticipate%20a%20recession%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-benchmark-revisions-labor-market-trade-leisure-hospitality-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20labor%20market%3C%2Fa%3E.%20While%20consumer%20spending%20has%20been%20doing%20quite%20well%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-market-layoffs-firing-hiring-slowdown-recession-job-listings-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20job%20market%20has%20been%20cooling%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202023%20and%202024%2C%20real%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20expanded%203.0%25%20and%203.1%25%2C%20respectively.%20Despite%20this%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20rose%20by%200.3%20percentage%20points%20in%20each%20of%20those%20two%20years.%20So%20far%20this%20year%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20on%20track%20to%20increase%20by%20another%200.3%20percentage%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKey%20areas%20of%20the%20jobs%20market%20appear%20to%20be%20slowing.%20First%2C%20the%20bulk%20of%20recent%20job%20growth%20has%20been%20in%20industries%20that%20are%20not%20correlated%20with%20the%20economic%20cycle%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flargest-job-growth-next-decade-healthcare-caregiving-tech-food-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esuch%20as%20healthcare%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20even%20in%20those%20still-expanding%20sectors%2C%20growth%20has%20been%20slowing%20lately.%20If%20that%20trend%20continues%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20see%20what%20other%20industries%20will%20be%20able%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20slack.%20Second%2C%20areas%20of%20the%20job%20market%20that%20follow%20the%20ups%20and%20downs%20of%20the%20broader%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20specifically%2C%20goods-producing%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20have%20already%20been%20contracting.%20Third%2C%20despite%20%26quot%3Bloose%26quot%3B%20financial%20conditions%2C%20such%20as%20a%20rising%20stock%20market%20and%20falling%20interest%20rates%2C%20which%20are%20generally%20thought%20to%20be%20supportive%20of%20hiring%2C%20labor%20markets%20have%20now%20reached%20a%20point%20where%20the%20level%20of%20unemployment%20exceeds%20the%20number%20of%20job%20vacancies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20consumption%20is%20the%20end-all%20and%20be-all%20of%20employment%20(%26quot%3Bsell%20more%20stuff%2C%20hire%20more%20people%26quot%3B)%2C%20why%20has%20the%20labor%20market%20slowed%20to%20begin%20with%3F%20There%20are%20clearly%20other%20areas%20of%20the%20economy%20that%20determine%20the%20strength%20in%20the%20labor%20market%20than%20just%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229bc171af-59c6-4670-9d8d-44d980271728%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20worrying%20slide%20of%20business%20investment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20of%20business%20investment%20is%20another%20reliable%20indicator%20of%20a%20recession.%20During%20a%20recession%2C%20nonresidential%20business%20investment%20%E2%80%94%20which%20excludes%20spending%20on%20homebuilding%20%E2%80%94%20always%20contracts%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fland-banking-new-home-construction-real-estate-prices-housing-builders-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eresidential%20investment%3C%2Fa%3E%20almost%20always%20declines%20(2001%20was%20the%20lone%20exception).%20Moreover%2C%20in%20the%20two%20quarters%20before%20a%20recession%2C%20the%20contribution%20of%20residential%20investment%20to%20GDP%20growth%20is%20negative%20(again%2C%20with%20the%20recession%20that%20followed%20the%202001%20tech%20bubble%20being%20an%20exception)%20while%20the%20contribution%20of%20nonresidential%20business%20investment%20tends%20to%20be%20positive.%20To%20the%20extent%20any%20one%20sector%20provides%20a%20tell%2C%20it's%20the%20homebuilders.%20And%2C%20bad%20news%2C%20residential%20investment%20has%20been%20contracting%20for%20five%20of%20the%20last%20six%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FgbuE3%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Bar%20Chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FgbuE3%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20drop%20in%20homebuilding%20investment%2C%20there%20is%20some%20possibility%20of%20a%20false%20signal.%20In%20fact%2C%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20residential%20investment%20has%20declined%20in%20the%20post-COVID%20era.%20In%202022%2C%20as%20an%20example%2C%20there%20was%20a%20notable%20decline%20in%20residential%20investment.%20However%2C%20there%20are%20some%20important%20distinctions%20between%20then%20and%20now%20that%20make%20this%20current%20decrease%20more%20concerning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGovernment%20spending%20and%20investment%20were%20a%20meaningful%20tailwind%20to%20GDP%20growth.%20By%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202022%2C%20government%20spending%20and%20investment%20were%20adding%20about%20as%20much%20to%20GDP%20as%20residential%20investment%20was%20subtracting.%20By%20contrast%2C%20government%20spending%20and%20investment%20have%20recently%20been%20slowing%2C%20resulting%20in%20a%20modest%20drag%20on%20GDP.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThrough%20most%20of%202023%2C%20units%20under%20construction%20were%20elevated.%20Even%20as%20they%20slowed%20new%20construction%2C%20homebuilders%20had%20a%20substantial%20backlog%20of%20homes%20to%20work%20through%20and%20continued%20to%20add%20construction%20workers%20to%20their%20ranks.%20Nowadays%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20no%20such%20backlog%20exists.%20With%20housing%20starts%20running%20below%20completions%2C%20units%20under%20construction%20have%20more%20room%20to%20decline.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFinally%2C%20households%20were%20still%20drawing%20down%20pandemic-era%20excess%20savings%2C%20supporting%20consumption%20at%20a%20time%20when%20housing%20was%20slowing.%20Pandemic-era%20excess%20saving%20was%20drawn%20down%20completely%20sometime%20in%202024.%20That%20puts%20the%20onus%20on%20labor%20incomes%20as%20the%20primary%20driver%20of%20consumption%20now.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20reasons%20to%20assume%20that%20the%20slowdown%20in%20residential%20construction%20might%20matter%20a%20little%20more%20for%20the%20broader%20outlook%20than%20it%20did%20before.%20Indeed%2C%20a%20crude%20analysis%20suggests%20that%20more%20layoffs%20could%20be%20on%20the%20way%20for%20residential%20construction%20jobs.%20As%20of%20August%202025%2C%20the%20ratio%20of%20people%20employed%20in%20residential%20construction%20to%20housing%20permits%20stands%20at%202.5%2C%20the%20highest%20level%20since%202012.%20This%20ratio%20is%20about%2010%25%20higher%20than%20its%20average%20in%202024%2C%20meaning%20there%20is%20likely%20a%20large%20pool%20of%20construction%20workers%20waiting%20around%20to%20do%20something.%20There's%20no%20need%20to%20hold%20onto%20workers%20who%20are%20not%20doing%20anything.%20To%20return%20this%20ratio%20to%20its%202024%20average%2C%20assuming%20the%20number%20of%20new%20monthly%20permits%20issued%20stays%20steady%2C%20implies%20a%20decline%20of%20304%2C000%20jobs.%20Spreading%20this%20over%20the%20year%20implies%20a%20decline%20of%2025%2C000%20jobs%20a%20month.%20Even%20if%20this%20is%20even%20half-right%2C%20it's%20still%20a%20significant%20headwind%2C%20considering%20private%20employment%20is%20running%20at%20just%2030%2C000%20a%20month