ints.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fjapan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJapan's%20stock%20markets%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20on%20a%20tear%20this%20year%2C%20and%20a%20fresh%20jolt%20of%20optimism%20has%20sent%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fnikkei_225%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENikkei%20225%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20record%20highs%20after%20Sanae%20Takaichi's%20victory%20to%20lead%20the%20ruling%20Liberal%20Democratic%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20Nikkei%20225%20gained%20as%20much%20as%201.2%25%20to%20over%2048%2C500%20in%20its%20second%20straight%20day%20of%20historic%20highs%20as%20traders%20piled%20in%20on%20the%20%26quot%3BTakaichi%20trade%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20wager%20on%20stronger%20stocks%2C%20rising%20bond%20yields%2C%20and%20a%20weaker%20yen%20that%20boosts%20exporters%20and%20corporate%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETraders%20are%20betting%20that%20Takaichi's%20pro-growth%2C%20pro-fiscal%20stance%20could%20revive%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshinzo-abe-dead-former-japan-prime-minister-shooting-details-obituary-2022-7%23%3A~%3Atext%3DLegacy%2Cat%2520revitalizing%2520Japan%2527s%2520deflationary%2520economy.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Espirit%20of%20Abenomics%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20new%20wave%20of%20stimulus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20that%20optimism%20may%20be%20misplaced%20due%20to%20structural%20limits%20and%20political%20constraints%2C%20analysts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20Takaichi%20administration's%20economic%20approach%20is%20merely%20an%20extension%20of%20Abenomics%2C%20it%20could%20be%20short-lived%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Naka%20Matsuzawa%2C%20Nomura's%20chief%20macro%20strategist%2C%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d5366d2b-2d79-4564-9bd0-086da08dc120%5C%22%3EAbenomics%20nostalgia%20vs%202025%20economic%20reality%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20caution%20is%20because%20Japan's%20economic%20backdrop%20is%20different%20than%20the%20early%20years%20under%20former%20Japanese%20prime%20minister%20Shinzo%20Abe%2C%20who%20started%20his%20second%20term%20in%202012.%20He%20stepped%20down%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20the%20dollar%20was%20trading%20at%2080%20against%20the%20Japanese%20yen%20and%20inflation%20was%20negative.%20However%2C%20consumer%20inflation%20is%20now%20running%20at%20around%203%25%2C%20and%20the%20dollar%20is%20trading%20at%20around%20the%20150%20level%20against%20the%20yen%2C%20which%20restricts%20both%20fiscal%20and%20monetary%20space%20for%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20wrote%20in%20a%20Sunday%20note%20that%20Takaichi%20%26quot%3Bhas%20consistently%20stated%20her%20support%20for%20a%20strategic%2C%20proactive%20fiscal%20policy.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20analysts%20said%20she%20has%20also%20indicated%20her%20intention%20to%20respect%20the%20current%20policy%20stance%20of%20the%20coalition%20government%2C%20which%20includes%20removing%20a%20consumption%20tax%20from%20her%20platform%20and%20financing%20inflation%20countermeasures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20therefore%20believe%20it%20is%20unlikely%20she%20will%20immediately%20adopt%20large-scale%20fiscal%20expansion%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldman's%20analysts%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20wrote%20that%20they%20expect%20Takaichi's%20victory%20not%20to%20impact%20the%20Bank%20of%20Japan's%20monetary%20policy%2C%20with%20the%20next%20rate%20hike%20still%20expected%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analysts'%20measured%20assessments%20come%20as%20the%20market%20grapples%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fjapan-stock-market-nikkei-rally-leadership-ai-oracle-boj-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJapan's%20stock%20market%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20has%20entered%20overdrive%20mode%20in%202025%20after%20several%20years%20of%20steady%20gains.%3C%2Fp%