C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e43fb3cc993f9955cfa323%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223686%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20denied%20Google's%20bid%20to%20temporarily%20stay%20parts%20of%20a%20lower%20court%20ruling%20that%20would%20overhaul%20the%20company's%20Play%20Store.%3Cp%3EFrancis%20Mascarenhas%2FREUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20denied%20a%20bid%20to%20stay%20parts%20of%20an%20antitrust%20ruling%20affecting%20Google's%20Play%20Store.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Play%20Store%20would%20need%20to%20allow%20third-party%20downloads%20and%20have%20other%20payment%20options.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEpic%20Games%20won%20a%20suit%20against%20Google%20in%202023%2C%20and%20the%20company%20has%20appealed%20at%20least%20twice%20since.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20Play%20Store%20is%20in%20for%20an%20overhaul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20denied%20Google's%20bid%20to%20temporarily%20block%20parts%20of%20a%20lower%20court%20ruling%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-app-store-android-third-party-epic-games-judge-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elegal%20fight%20with%20Epic%20Games%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20maker%20of%20Fortnite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Alphabet-owned%20company%20had%20sought%20to%20pause%20orders%20from%20the%20Northern%20District%20Court%20of%20California%20that%20required%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eit%20to%20open%20its%20app%20ecosystem%20to%20rivals%2C%20stop%20restricting%20third-party%20downloads%2C%20and%20allow%20developers%20to%20steer%20users%20toward%20cheaper%20payment%20options%20outside%20Google's%20billing%20system.%20For%20Android%20users%2C%20this%20would%20mean%20being%20able%20to%20access%20apps%20directly%20from%20developers%20outside%20the%20Play%20Store%2C%20at%20price%20points%20chosen%20by%20the%20developers%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20justices%20did%20not%20comment%20on%20why%20they%20denied%20Google's%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAndroid%20provides%20more%20choice%20for%20users%20and%20developers%20than%20any%20mobile%20OS%2C%20and%20the%20changes%20ordered%20by%20the%20US%20District%20Court%20will%20jeopardize%20users'%20ability%20to%20safely%20download%20apps%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Google%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20we're%20disappointed%20the%20order%20isn't%20stayed%2C%20we%20will%20continue%20our%20appeal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20dispute%20stems%20from%20a%202020%20lawsuit%20in%20which%20Epic%20Games%20sued%20Google%2C%20alleging%20that%20the%20company%20was%20running%20an%20illegal%20monopoly%20over%20its%20Android%20app%20download%20restrictions%20and%20in-app%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202023%2C%20a%20California%20jury%20ruled%20in%20favor%20of%20Epic%20Games%2C%20finding%20that%20Google's%20policies%20for%20the%20Play%20Store%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-loses-app-store-antitrust-suit-against-fortnite-creators-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eviolated%20antitrust%20laws%3C%2Fa%3E.%20US%20District%20Judge%20James%20Donato%20then%20ordered%20Google%20to%20open%20Android%20to%20competing%20app%20stores%20and%20allow%20developers%20to%20use%20their%20own%20billing%20systems%20for%20a%20period%20of%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20upheld%20that%20verdict.%20In%20September%2C%20Google%20filed%20a%20stay%2C%20requesting%20that%20the%20ordered%20remedies%20be%20put%20on%20hold%20while%20the%20company%20works%20on%20filing%20a%20full%20appeal%20with%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20by%20October%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court's%20rejection%20of%20Google's%20request%20means%20that%20the%20lower%20court's%20orders%20must%20be%20implemented%20by%20October%2022.%20The%20changes%20will%20remain%20unless%20Google's%20full%20appeal%20to%20